# Superpowers Skills — Cline Integration

Skills live in `.superpowers/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. Read the full SKILL.md
when invoking a skill. Announce: "Using [skill] to [purpose]."

## Bootstrap

If you think there is even a 1% chance a skill might apply, you MUST invoke it
BEFORE any response or action — including clarifying questions, exploring the
codebase, or checking files.

Skill check priority:
- "Let's build X" → brainstorming first, then implementation.
- "Fix this bug" → systematic-debugging first.
- "Write tests" → test-driven-development.
- Multi-step task with spec → writing-plans, then executing-plans.

User instructions (direct requests) take precedence over skills.

## Red Flags — these thoughts mean STOP

| Thought | Reality |
|---------|---------|
| "This is just a simple question" | Questions are tasks. Check for skills. |
| "I need more context first" | Skill check comes BEFORE clarifying questions. |
| "Let me explore the codebase first" | Skills tell you HOW to explore. Check first. |
| "This doesn't need a formal skill" | If a skill exists, use it. |
| "The skill is overkill" | Simple things become complex. Use it. |
| "I'll just do this one thing first" | Check BEFORE doing anything. |

## Skill Index

| Skill | Trigger |
|-------|---------|
| using-superpowers | Every conversation start (this file) |
| brainstorming | Before any creative/feature work |
| test-driven-development | Before implementing any feature or bugfix |
| systematic-debugging | Bug, test failure, unexpected behavior |
| writing-plans | Multi-step task with spec, before code |
| executing-plans | Have written plan, ready to implement |
| subagent-driven-development | Plan ready, subagents available |
| dispatching-parallel-agents | Multiple independent tasks |
| requesting-code-review | Before asking for review |
| receiving-code-review | When receiving review feedback |
| using-git-worktrees | Parallel development branches |
| finishing-a-development-branch | Tasks complete, ready to merge |
| verification-before-completion | Before declaring fix done |
| writing-skills | Creating new skills |
